In this article, President Biden addresses the recent losses and tragedies in the country, including the passing of his friend Alcee Hastings and the shooting of Daunte Wright. He emphasizes the need for real change and discusses the focus on equity in every aspect of the government. Biden mentions the importance of addressing income and economic opportunity, not just prisons, when it comes to advancing equality. He expresses his commitment to discussing the priorities of the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) and the American Jobs Act. Biden also mentions the reduction of child poverty and poverty in Black communities through recent legislation and his objective of making those changes permanent. The article ends with Biden addressing questions about the Johnson & Johnson vaccine and expressing confidence in the availability of enough vaccines for every American.